Been playing a bit with realfuels lately.

Is there an easy way to stop make the fuels boil off, with a module manager config, or do you manually need to set that for each fuel in the config? Or is there a true/false in some config?

Hope for answer

- - - Updated - - -

I've seen in my real fuels map, there is a "RealTankTypes.cfg".

All the resources with boiloff has a "loss_rate" tag with number after it.

Is there a way I can make module manager find all of those and put "//" before it or "0" behind it?

Tried to look on the MM wiki, but didn't get any wiser :/

Something like @TANK_DEFINITION,*:FINAL { @TANK,* { @loss_rate = 0 } } should work.

Put that in the top of the config, and I still have boiloff. Seperate .cfg file didn't work either.
